Linked List: Linear DS -> Non-contiguous -> Sequential access.
It can be used for large lists and for dynamic storage.

struct ListNode{
  int val;
  struct ListNode* next;
}

struct DoublyLinkedList{
  int val;
  struct DoublyLinkedList *next, *prev;
}

Whenever we want to create a new list or return a new list, then make dummy pointers.
